  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "POWER MANAGEMENT NOTES (v1.1):\n\n1) Power tree:\n   J2 (USB-C) → VBUS_USB (5V) → BQ24075 (charger) → VBAT (3.7V LiPo)\n   VBAT → U6 RT9193-33GB → 3V3_MAIN  (digital logic)\n   VBAT → U7 LP2985-33   → 3V3_ANALOG (SI4732 VA/VDDO, ES7243E AVDD)\n   3V3_ANALOG → U8 MIC5504-1.8 → 1V8_SI4732 (SI4732 VDD)\n   VBAT → FB1(audio_output.kicad_sch) → PVDD_FILT (MAX98357A PVDD)\n\n2) LDO selection:\n   [FIXED] U6: RT9193-33GB (was TLV75533PDBVR)\n     - TLV75533: Vdrop=200mV typ → dropout at VBAT=3.5V\n     - RT9193-33GB: Vdrop=150mV typ → holds until VBAT=3.45V\n     - Improvement: 50mV more headroom at low battery\n     - Pin-compatible SOT-23-5: IN-OUT-GND-EN-N.C. same pinout\n   U7: LP2985 kept (only 150mA needed, <30uVrms noise)\n\n3) Charge current: R10=2kΩ → I_charge = 890mV/2kΩ = 445mA (BQ24075 datasheet)\n\n4) Capacitor downsizing summary [FIX v1.1]:\n   All 10uF 0805 bulk decoupling caps changed to 4.7uF 0603 X5R:\n   C25 (U6 input), C27 (U6 output), C26 (U7 input), C28 (U7 output)\n   C_U5_IN (BQ24075 VCC input), C_VBAT (VBAT output)\n   C_CP2 (CP2102N bulk) — in esp32_core sheet\n   4.7uF/6.3V 0603 X5R: adequate for decoupling, 20% footprint of 0805\n\n5) LP2985 stability note:\n   Datasheet requires ≥1uF output cap; 4.7uF X5R OK (no NMC instability)\n   Do NOT use Y5V/Z5U (large derate at voltage)\n\n[FIX LOG v1.1 - 2026-04-28]\n  LDO-BRN: TLV75533 200mV dropout → Brownout when VBAT<3.5V (~15% SOC)\n  FIX: RT9193-33GB (150mV dropout) → survives to VBAT=3.45V (~10% SOC)\n  CAP-SIZE: 10uF 0805 at all bulk nodes → 4.7uF 0603 X5R (body area -60%)"
    (at 245 90)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
